article.headline: Sacred Heart 42, Assumption 21
article.story: Sacred Heart comes back to beat Assumption 42-21 FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- Ervin Jones rushed for 210 yards and four touchdowns, leading Sacred Heart to a 42-21 victory today (Saturday) over Assumption in the season opener for both schools. The senior tailback ran the ball 22 times and scored on runs of 5, 50, 9 and 42 yards. Josh Ratacik completed 19 of 38 passes for 190 yards with two interceptions for Assumption. The Greyhounds took an early 14-0 lead. But Sacred Heart responded with 28 unanswered points. After Assumption cut the lead to 28-21 on a 9-yard run by Herbert Woodward, Jones took over, scoring twice in the final 8 minutes.
